                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13666.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-02T00:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1914, midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Convention to-day approved the committee report outlined in my October 30, 11
                    p.m., and a committee of six was named to visit Carranza and officially inform
                    him of Convention’s action; Villa will be similarly informed. Villa telegraphed
                    President Gutiérrez this morning reiterating allegiance and placing himself
                    under his orders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
